cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper involves the use of machine learning techniques to improve the detection of credit card fraudulent transactions. Specifically, it uses Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) to generate artificial data to assist with classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the paper deals with fraudulent transactions. Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques to generate realistic fraudulent transactions. Finally, GANs are a type of neural network, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
